    <% include ../partials/head.ejs %>

</head>

<body>

<% include ../partials/menu.ejs %>

<div tabindex="-1" id="content" class="site-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Tech Radar (alpha)</h1>
        <p>Practical team technology management</p>
        <p>*The data in this site is for test only*</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container bs-docs-container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding-left: 15px;">
            <h1 class="page-header">Overview</h1>
            <p class="lead">A platform to allow teams to gather thoughts and views on technologies.
                Both the ones they are using and emerging technologies</p>
            <p class="lead">Everyone can <a href="#addtechnology">add</a>, <a href="#comment">comment</a> and <a
                        href="#vote">vote</a> on technologies, with <a href="#reports">reports</a> generated from the
                community's response</p>

        </div>
    </div>


    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12" align="center" style="padding-top: 40px;">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-down" aria-hidden="true"/>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="panel panel-default" id="addtechnology">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">Add a technology</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    Anyone can add a technology to the catalogue, the more the merrier.
                    Once added anyone can comment and vote on its status.
                    Should it be 'Adopted' , 'Assessed' or 'Avoided' ? You decide...
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12" align="center">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-down" aria-hidden="true"/>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="panel panel-default" id="comment">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">Comment</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    Add a comment or experience to a technology to help the assessment as to how successful it's use has
                    been.
                    This should include guidance,hints,tips and pitfalls of the technology for future projects.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12" align="center">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-down" aria-hidden="true"/>
        </div>
    </div>


    <div class="row" id="vote">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">Vote</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    Vote whether you think each technology should be 'Adopted', 'Assessed' or 'Avoided'.
                    The votes and comments are assessed, with the final status of a technology being assigned manually.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12" align="center">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-down" aria-hidden="true"/>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row"  id="reports">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">Reports</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    Results of the voting and comments. Displays simple a table and chart showing whether individual
                    technologies should be adopted, assessed or avoided.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div><!-- /.container -->

<% include ../partials/footer.ejs %>
</body>
</html>
